column2: A hardware error of the module
column3: Switch power off, then on again. If the error recurs, the module may have failed. Consult the Mitsubishi office.

column2: The setting of the intelligent function module switch 5 is other than 0.
column3: Set 0 for the intelligent function module switch 5 in the parameter setting of GX Developer.

column2: An invalid value is set in the offset/gain setting. The number of the error channel can not be identified.
column3:
Perform the offset/gain setting again for all of the
channels that use the user range settings. 
If the error occurs again, the module may be malfunctioning. 
Please consult your local Mitsubishi representative, explaining the detailed description of the problem.

column2: The G(P).OGSTOR instruction was executed in the offset/gain setting mode.
column3: Do not execute the G(P).OGSTOR instruction in the offset/gain setting mode.

column2:
*The G(P).OGSTOR instruction was executed consecutively.
* At the time of offset/gain setting, a set value was written to the flash memory 26 or more times.
column3:
* Execute the G(P).OGSTOR instruction only once for one module.
* At the time of offset/gain setting, write a set value only once at one time.

column2:
* The G(P).OGSTOR instruction was executed for the model that differs from the model for which the G(P).OGLOAD instruction had been executed. 
* The G(P).OGSTOR instruction had been executed before the G(P).OGLOAD instruction was executed.
column3:
* Execute the G(P).OGLOAD and G(P).OGSTOR instructions for the same model.
* Execute the G(P).OGLOAD instruction first, then G(P).OGSTOR instruction.
